# Mobile UI — PARKED (P7-14 / ES3-13)

Mobile phone layout work is **intentionally paused**. Do not implement, refactor, or commit changes to mobile-specific code unless the user explicitly asks to restart the mobile sprint.

## What is parked

- `ItineraryDayPlannerView.tsx` — `isMobile`, `matchMedia('(max-width: 640px)')`, `mobileNav`, `mobileDayStack`, `mobileTrackRow`
- `ItineraryDayPlannerView.module.css` — `.mobileNav`, `.mobileDayStack`, `.mobileTrackRow`
- Any new mobile shell, hooks, or cut-down layouts

## Where future mobile work should go

When mobile restarts, prefer new files under `src/_parked/mobile/` (gitignored) or a dedicated branch — not ad-hoc edits scattered in desktop components until the shell design is agreed.

## Still allowed without mobile sprint

- Desktop and iPad behaviour (full UI per functional spec §31.2)
- Unrelated bug fixes in shared components if they do not change mobile breakpoints or `isMobile` branches
- CSS `@media` tweaks in journal/shared summary only if required for a desktop bug — flag to user if touch mobile layout

